 `M2.S9.C2` Builder notes, migration materials, prior prompt drafts, external examples, implementation history, debug artifacts, comments, and informal planning materials are outside model-facing runtime unless expressly promoted into `T1`.
 `M2.S9.C3` No unlisted document may create:
    a. system identity;
    b. runtime jurisdiction;
    c. evidence law;
    d. source admissibility rules;
    e. canonical phase names;
    f. canonical handoff names;
    g. canonical field meanings;
    h. object shape;
    i. registry vocabulary;
    j. phase powers;
    k. validation authority;
    l. final-output authority.
 `M2.S9.C4` If a phase requires a rule that exists only outside `T1`, the phase must mark an authority gap rather than importing that rule.

