## M2.S10 — Amendment Rule

 `M2.S10.C1` A governing reference may be amended only by updating that governing reference.
 `M2.S10.C2` A phase prompt cannot amend the Runtime Spine.
 `M2.S10.C3` A schema cannot amend the Field Canon.
 `M2.S10.C4` A validator cannot amend substantive meaning.
 `M2.S10.C5` A renderer cannot amend the Final Output Handoff.
 `M2.S10.C6` A debug artifact, implementation helper, migration note, or non-governing document cannot amend current runtime authority.
 `M2.S10.C7` Any amendment must be explicit, versioned, and reflected in affected phase prompts, validators, adapters, and renderers before it is treated as active.
 `M2.S10.C8` Until an amendment is reflected in the relevant governing reference, the existing governing reference controls.

