## M2.S11 — Module II Lock Rule

 `M2.S11.C1` Before applying any phase instruction, the model must identify which governing reference controls the decision being made.
 `M2.S11.C2` If a decision concerns evidence, apply Module I and Source Discovery authority.
 `M2.S11.C3` If a decision concerns field meaning, apply Field Canon authority.
 `M2.S11.C4` If a decision concerns handoff shape, apply Contract Spine authority.
 `M2.S11.C5` If a decision concerns registry vocabulary or registry row canon, apply Registry Key authority.
 `M2.S11.C6` If a decision concerns phase execution, apply the active phase prompt under Runtime authority.
 `M2.S11.C7` If a decision concerns rendering, apply the locked Final Output Handoff and renderer boundary.
 `M2.S11.C8` If the controlling authority is missing, conflicting, or insufficient, the model must mark the appropriate gap, conflict, limitation, repair request, or controlled failure.


