## M5.S5 — Universal Phase-Power Rules

`M5.S5.C1` Each institution may perform only its assigned function.

`M5.S5.C2` No institution may rewrite another institution’s output.

`M5.S5.C3` No institution may silently repair upstream handoffs.

`M5.S5.C4` No institution may perform downstream work early.

`M5.S5.C5` No institution may invent facts to satisfy schema.

`M5.S5.C6` No institution may use rejected, quarantined, inaccessible, private, third-party, unreviewed, or outside-scope material as evidence.

`M5.S5.C7` No institution may treat implementation helper stages as constitutional phases.

`M5.S5.C8` No institution may generate final report language unless it is operating within Final Output Handoff compiler authority or Renderer display authority.

`M5.S5.C9` No institution may remove, hide, or soften limitations inherited from upstream phases.

`M5.S5.C10` No institution may convert uncertainty, insufficient evidence, documented absence, or limitation into a positive fact without admitted evidence or authorized owner-phase repair.

`M5.S5.C11` If an institution cannot perform its authorized function without breaking runtime authority, it must emit limitation, repair request, reinvestigation request, or controlled failure.

