## M5.S7 — Cross-Phase Contamination Rule

`M5.S7.C1` Cross-phase contamination occurs when an institution performs work owned by another institution.

`M5.S7.C2` Examples of cross-phase contamination include:

a. Target Profiling inventing feature/function details;
b. Feature Profiling rewriting target identity;
c. Feature Profiling assigning registry statuses;
d. Legal Cartography giving enforceability conclusions;
e. Legal Cartography inventing missing clauses;
f. Data Provenance rewriting feature inventory;
g. Data Provenance inferring private data practices;
