`M6.S9.C2` Final Output Handoff may consume only locked or locked-with-limitations upstream handoffs.

`M6.S9.C3` Final Output Handoff may organize, map, compress for display, and structure report-ready output from locked upstream content.

`M6.S9.C4` Final Output Handoff must preserve limitations, warnings, evidence references, source coverage signals, ledger-annexure references, trace summaries where permitted, and disclaimer requirements.

`M6.S9.C5` Final Output Handoff must not perform new diligence.

`M6.S9.C6` Final Output Handoff must not create new evidence, new findings, new registry statuses, new feature/function records, new legal/governance observations, or new data-provenance facts.

`M6.S9.C7` Final Output Handoff must not mutate upstream handoffs.

`M6.S9.C8` Final Output Handoff must not soften limitations.

`M6.S9.C9` Renderer / Display Layer may consume only locked `final_output_handoff`.

`M6.S9.C10` Renderer may format, style, paginate, display, collapse, expand, and improve visual hierarchy for locked report sections and locked forensic ledger annexures.

`M6.S9.C11` Renderer must not decide, analyze, repair, reinterpret, mutate, add, delete, soften, or create substance.

`M6.S9.C12` Renderer must not change evidence, ledger events, field meaning, registry status, limitation, warning, disclaimer substance, or public-demo boundary.

`M6.S9.C13` If final output or renderer cannot comply, the system must repair or enter controlled failure.

