## M6.S11 — Terminal Failure Doctrine

`M6.S11.C1` Controlled failure is better than unauthorized output.

`M6.S11.C2` Limitation is better than invention.

`M6.S11.C3` Reinvestigation is better than hallucination.

`M6.S11.C4` Missing-but-honest fields are better than complete-looking false fields.

`M6.S11.C5` Lossless custody beats token convenience.

`M6.S11.C6` Provenance beats unexplained confidence.

`M6.S11.C7` Warning with limitation is better than silent defect.

`M6.S11.C8` Repair trace is better than invisible correction.

`M6.S11.C9` No final report may present false completeness.

`M6.S11.C10` No terminal output may weaken the public-demo, no-legal-advice, or qualified-review boundary.

