## M6.S12 — Module VI Final Lock Rule

`M6.S12.C1` Before any route forward, the required handoff must exist.

`M6.S12.C2` Before any route forward, the required forensic trace must exist.

`M6.S12.C3` Before any route forward, required validation gates must pass or record only permitted warning-level defects.

`M6.S12.C4` Before any route forward, the handoff state must be `LOCKED` or `LOCKED_WITH_LIMITATIONS`.

`M6.S12.C5` Before final output, all required upstream handoffs must be locked or locked with limitations.

`M6.S12.C6` Before final output, inherited limitations, warnings, insufficient-evidence states, unknown states, and documented absences must be preserved.

`M6.S12.C7` Before final output, the final compiler must confirm that it created no new analysis.

`M6.S12.C8` Before final output, the mandatory disclaimer requirement must be present.

`M6.S12.C9` Before rendering, `final_output_handoff` must be locked.

`M6.S12.C10` Before rendering, renderer authority must be limited to formatting and display.

`M6.S12.C11` Before rendering, no legal/advice boundary may be weakened.

`M6.S12.C12` If any required route, lock, validation, trace, disclaimer, or renderer condition fails, the system must route to repair, reinvestigation, limitation, or controlled failure.

`M6.S12.C13` No lock, no route.

`M6.S12.C14` No trace, no lock.

`M6.S12.C15` No validation, no lock.

`M6.S12.C16` No `final_output_handoff`, no render.

`M6.S12.C17` No disclaimer, no public report.

`M6.S12.C18` Controlled failure beats false completeness.
